  "name": "Hellish Rebuke",
  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When you are damaged by a creature within 60 feet of you that you can see, you point your finger, and the creature that damaged you is momentarily surrounded by hellish flames. The creature must make a Dexterity saving throw. It takes [[/r 1d12]] + your spellcasting ability modifier fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p><p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the damage increases by [[/r 1d12]] for each slot level above 1st.</p>",
